    "summary": "I am a lightning scientist at ASTRON (the Netherlands Institute for Radio Astronomy). \n\nI am interested in atmospheric physics, electrodynamics, and computer programming. I am in seventh-heaven when I get to work on a project that involves all three of these areas.\n\nProfessionally, I am using data collected by the LOFAR radio telescope, located in northern Netherlands, to map the 3-dimensional structure of lightning flashes, and to probe in the internal structure of lightning leaders. My graduate studies were at the International Center for Lightning Research and Testing where we would trigger lightning by launching grounded rockets. During my PhD I studied Terrestrial Gamma Ray Flashes and the interactions between cosmic rays and lightning initiation.",
